Step 1: Create a Maven Project

Open Command Prompt and run:

mvn archetype:generate -DgroupId=com.example -DartifactId=maven-example -DarchetypeArtifactId=maven-archetype-quickstart -DinteractiveMode=false

This command creates a Maven project named maven-example.

Step 2: Navigate to Project Folder
cd maven-example
Step 3: Open and Edit pom.xml File

Open the pom.xml file:

notepad pom.xml

Replace the content with:

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<project xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0"
         xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
         xsi:schemaLocation="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 
         http://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd">

    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>

    <groupId>com.example</groupId>
    <artifactId>maven-example</artifactId>
    <version>1.0-SNAPSHOT</version>

    <dependencies>
        <dependency>
            <groupId>junit</groupId>
            <artifactId>junit</artifactId>
            <version>4.12</version>
            <scope>test</scope>
        </dependency>
    </dependencies>

    <build>
        <plugins>
            <plugin>
                <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
                <artifactId>maven-compiler-plugin</artifactId>
                <version>3.8.1</version>

                <configuration>
                    <source>1.8</source>
                    <target>1.8</target>
                </configuration>

            </plugin>
        </plugins>
    </build>

</project>

Save and close the file.

Step 4: Create App.java File

Navigate to:

src/main/java/com/example/

Open App.java and replace the content with:

package com.example;

public class App {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        System.out.println("Hello, Maven");
        System.out.println("This is the simple realworld example....");

        int a = 5;
        int b = 10;

        System.out.println("Sum of " + a + " and " + b + " is " + sum(a, b));
    }

    public static int sum(int x, int y) {
        return x + y;
    }
}

Save the file.

Step 5: Build the Maven Project

Make sure you are inside the project folder:

cd maven-example

Run:

mvn clean install

This command:

Cleans old files
Compiles source code
Runs tests
Builds the JAR file
Step 6: Run the Maven Project

Execute the application using:

mvn exec:java -Dexec.mainClass="com.example.App"
Maven Output
Hello, Maven
This is the simple realworld example....
Sum of 5 and 10 is 15
Step 7: Migrate Maven Project to Gradle

Inside the same project directory, run:

gradle init

You will see:

Found a Maven build. Generate a Gradle build from this? (default: yes)

Type:

yes

Next:

Select build script DSL:
1: Kotlin
2: Groovy

Type:

2

Next:

Generate build using new APIs and behavior? (default: no)

Type:

no

Gradle configuration files will be generated.

Step 8: Edit build.gradle File

Open:

notepad build.gradle

Replace the content with:

plugins {
    id 'java'
}

group = 'com.example'
version = '1.0-SNAPSHOT'

repositories {
    mavenCentral()
}

dependencies {
    testImplementation 'junit:junit:4.12'
}

task run(type: JavaExec) {
    main = 'com.example.App'
    classpath = sourceSets.main.runtimeClasspath
}

Save the file.

Step 9: Build the Gradle Project

Run:

gradlew build

This command:

Compiles the Java source code
Runs tests
Creates build files
Step 10: Run the Gradle Application

Execute:

gradlew run
Gradle Output
Hello, Maven
This is the simple realworld example....
Sum of 5 and 10 is 15
